  "prompt": "I love her a lot but her past troubles me and I don't trust her. Please read comment. What should I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry you're going through this. Relationships can be challenging, especially when it comes to trust and dealing with past issues. Here are a few steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Communication**: Sit down and have an honest conversation with her about your feelings. Explain how her past is affecting your trust and your relationship. Express your concerns without blaming her, and listen to her side of the story too.\n\n2. **Understanding**: Remember that everyone has a past, and we all make mistakes. Try to understand the circumstances that led to her actions and whether she has genuinely changed since then.\n\n3. **Self-reflection**: Reflect on why you find it difficult to trust her. Is it because of past experiences of your own? Are there specific behaviors that make you uneasy?\n\n4. **Boundaries**: Set clear boundaries that can help you feel more secure in the relationship. For example, discussing what is acceptable and what is not moving forward.\n\n5. **Professional help**: Consider seeking counseling or therapy. A professional can offer guidance on trust issues and help you both work through them.\n\n6. **Evaluate**: After you\u2019ve tried these steps, evaluate whether the relationship is providing you with the emotional security and happiness you need. If her past continuously brings you distress and negatively impacts your trust, it might be necessary to reassess the relationship. \n\nIt\u2019s important that both partners feel valued and secure. Trust is crucial, and if you find it difficult to regain it despite efforts, making a decision that prioritizes your emotional well-being may be necessary.",
